CEDA and odc-stac

Minimal reproducible example of using odc-stac with the CEDA STAC API. I like using uv to manage my Python dependencies:

uv venv
source .venv/bin/activate
uv pip install ipykernel odc-stac pystac-client pystac[jinja2] rasterio dask[distrubuted] bokeh rioxarray

pystac[jinja2] enables pretty-printing of pystac items.

import os

import dask.distributed
import odc.stac
import rasterio
from pystac.extensions.raster import RasterBand
from pystac_client import Client
os.environ["PYDEVD_DISABLE_FILE_VALIDATION"] = (
    "1"  # this is to silence some yelling for @gadomski
)

client = dask.distributed.Client()
client

client = Client.open("https://api.stac.ceda.ac.uk/")
item_collection = client.search(
    collections=["sentinel2_ard"],
    intersects={"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-1.3144, 51.5755]},
    sortby="-properties.datetime",
    max_items=10,
).item_collection()

A naïve load raises an exception.

odc.stac.load(item_collection)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
ValueError                                Traceback (most recent call last)
Cell In[4], line 1
----> 1 odc.stac.load(item_collection)

File ~/miniforge3/envs/eodh/lib/python3.12/site-packages/odc/stac/_load.py:507, in load(items, bands, groupby, resampling, dtype, chunks, pool, crs, resolution, anchor, geobox, bbox, lon, lat, x, y, like, geopolygon, progress, fail_on_error, stac_cfg, patch_url, preserve_original_order, **kw)
    489 gbox = output_geobox(
    490     _parsed,
    491     bands=bands,
   (...)
    503     y=y,
    504 )
    506 if gbox is None:
--> 507     raise ValueError("Failed to auto-guess CRS/resolution.")
    509 debug = kw.get("debug", False)
    511 # Check we have all the bands of interest
    512 # will raise ValueError if no such band/alias

ValueError: Failed to auto-guess CRS/resolution.

The STAC items don’t have the projection or raster extensions, so odc-stac will refuse to compute the “geobox” 😔. odc-stac pretty opinionated on what STAC items and assets should look like. Let’s add those extensions.

for item in item_collection.items:
    asset = item.assets["cog"]
    cog = rasterio.open(asset.href)
    epsg = cog.crs.to_epsg()
    dtypes = cog.dtypes
    shape = cog.shape
    transform = list(cog.transform)

    item.ext.add("proj")
    item.ext.add("raster")

    item.ext.proj.epsg = epsg

    cog = item.assets["cog"]
    cog.ext.raster.bands = [RasterBand.create(data_type=dtype) for dtype in dtypes]
    cog.ext.proj.shape = shape
    cog.ext.proj.transform = transform

Now it should work! We pass chunks={} to enable Dask.

bbox = [-1.2, 51.6, -1.1, 51.7]
dataset = odc.stac.load(item_collection, bands=("red", "green", "blue"), chunks={}, bbox=bbox)
